## v1.8.0 (2026-04-25)

**Changed by:** ProjectKeystone 180-issue C++20 myrmidon swarm (7 EASY waves + 9 MEDIUM waves, 2026-04-25)
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed
- Added ProjectKeystone 2026-04-25 session summary row (C++20 swarm, 180 issues)
- Added 7 new Failed Attempts entries:
  - Conan + cnats: missing libssl-dev in Dockerfile builder stage blocks CMake build
  - TSan + concurrentqueue: fundamental incompatibility (false positives) — classify as HARD
  - enable_shared_from_this diamond inheritance when base class already inherits it
  - Two agents both modifying CMakeLists.txt in the same wave despite grouping rules
  - Adding @pytest.mark.asyncio decorators when asyncio_mode='auto' in pyproject.toml
  - Trusting agent-reported PR numbers (wrong in 3/16 waves)
  - pixi.lock commit requirement confirmed again (pre-existing entry, reconfirmed)
- Added new "C++20/Conan/pixi Project-Specific Guards" subsection in Results & Parameters with 6-item checklist and ready-to-run bash commands
- Added "When to Use" condition #10: C++20/CMake/Conan projects trigger C++20 guard checks
- Added ProjectKeystone session statistics table
- Added HomericIntelligence/ProjectKeystone to Verified On table
- Updated description to mention C++20/Conan/pixi-specific guards
- Updated Overview outcome to mention C++20 guards
- Bumped version 1.7.0 → 1.8.0, updated date to 2026-04-25

### Why
ProjectKeystone 180-issue swarm (2026-04-25) revealed 7 C++20/Conan/pixi-specific failure
modes not previously captured:
1. libssl-dev missing in Dockerfile builder stage: Conan resolves transitive OpenSSL deps
   silently; system headers still needed by compiler. Non-obvious from conanfile.py.
2. TSan + concurrentqueue: lock-free atomics trigger TSan false positives by design.
   Issues requiring TSan + concurrentqueue must be HARD — no agent fix possible without
   replacing the dependency.
3. enable_shared_from_this diamond inheritance: derived class added it when base already
   had it; caused "ambiguous base class" compile error. Must grep hierarchy first.
4. CMakeLists.txt double-agent: despite same-file grouping rule, two agents both modified
   CMakeLists.txt (SPDX + spdlog looked unrelated). Rule extended: CMakeLists.txt is a
   hard anchor like ci.yml — one agent per wave, always.
5. asyncio_mode='auto' + @pytest.mark.asyncio: redundant decorator when auto mode active
   causes deprecation warnings. Must check pyproject.toml before writing tests.
6. Agent PR number unreliability: 3/16 waves had wrong reported numbers. gh pr list is
   the only reliable ground truth after each wave.

