## v1.3.0 (2026-04-23)

**Changed by:** HomericIntelligence/Odysseus 35-issue triage session (19 resolved: 17 PRs + 2 ALREADY-DONE closures)
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed
- Added session summary row for HomericIntelligence/Odysseus 35-issue triage (2026-04-23)
- Added 4 new Failed Attempts entries:
  - PR number collision from parallel agents (stale agent-reported PR numbers)
  - Worktree creation failure on symlink-heavy repo (12 submodules timeout)
  - Agent branch naming drift (Haiku using title-slug instead of `<N>-auto-impl`)
  - Two agents merging into same PR branch (parallel worktree race condition)
- Added HomericIntelligence/Odysseus to Verified On table

### Why
Odysseus 35-issue myrmidon swarm session revealed three new failure patterns not documented in prior sessions:
1. Parallel agents in the same repo both reported "PR #120" — stale numbers in agent output. `gh pr list` is ground truth.
2. Worktree creation timed out on Odysseus (12 submodule symlinks) — fallback to main worktree + manual branch return worked.
3. Haiku agent for #18 used `18-fix-runbook` instead of `18-auto-impl` — must spell out exact branch name in Run: step.
4. Agents for #50 and #53 both committed to `50-auto-impl` in parallel — both issues closed but PR was messy.

